-- New York Yankees Invite 27 Players to Bring Spring Training Roster to 67
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-02-09T05:01:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/new-york-yankees-invite-27-players-to-bring-spring-training-roster-to-67.html
The  New York Yankees  invited 27
players, including 13 signed to minor-league contracts, to
spring training camp.  The 14 pitchers, five infielders, five catchers and three
outfielders will join 40 roster players at Steinbrenner Field in
Tampa,  Florida .  Among the minor-league players are infielders Russell Branyan and Bill Hall, pitchers Manny Delcarmen and Hideki Okajima and outfielder Dewayne Wise.  The Yankees start their spring schedule with a game against
the University of South Florida on March 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
